"Renegade Master" was Wildchild's first hit single in 1995, peaking at No. 11 on the UK Singles Chart, but was surpassed by the success of Fatboy Slim's remix "Renegade Master '98", which peaked at No. 3 in 1998.
On 6 April 1996, his girlfriend Donna Snell gave birth to their son, Noir.
The tracks "Jump to My Beat", "Renegade Master" (famously sampling "One for the Trouble" by A.D.O.R.) and the subsequent "Renegade Master '98" were his most successful.
Fatboy Slim's 1998 Old Skool Mix is perhaps the most famous version of "Renegade Master".
